CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 24, 1946 reads: " "I Love You Truly" - Miss Estelle Stephens, daughter of Mr. and Mrs. Fred Stephens of Beltzhoover, became the bride of James W. Ewing, son of Mr. and Mrs. J. Dye of McKees Rocks, recently in an impressive ceremony performed at the home of the bride. The Rev. Ralph Reynolds officiated. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Bride Estelle Stephens Ewing and groom James W. Ewing standing behind four tiered wedding cake, in home of Mr. and Mrs. Fred Stephens
